Software Used
MATLAB R2025a with Audio toolbox, Deep Learning.


Hardware parts used
• Esp32 wroom32
• Arduino
• Arduino motor driver L293D
• Lipo batterys


Algorithm

1. Start the System
• Power on the robot car and connect the ESP32 to Wi-Fi.
• Upload Arduino code to ESP32 for communication between MATLAB and
motor driver.

2. Initialize MATLAB
• Open MATLAB and run the v.m script.
• Start audio input (microphone) using Audio Toolbox.

3. Voice Command Acquisition
• MATLAB continuously listens for the user’s voice command.
• Speech is recorded using audiorecorder function.

4. Speech-to-Text Conversion
• The captured audio is processed and converted into text.
• Predefined keywords like "forward", "backward", "left", "right", "stop"
are recognized.

5. Command Verification
• Compare recognized text with predefined commands.
• If the word matches a valid command → proceed.
• If invalid command → prompt user to repeat.

6. Send Command to ESP32
• MATLAB sends the recognized command over Wi-Fi (TCP/IP Socket) to
ESP32.
• ESP32 receives command string from MATLAB.

7. ESP32 → Arduino Motor Driver
• ESP32 forwards the command to the Arduino motor shield (AFMotor
library).
• Depending on the command:
forward → both motors rotate forward
backward → both motors rotate backward
left → left motor stop, right motor forward
right → right motor stop, left motor forward
stop → both motors stop

8. Robot Movement
Car performs the required motion according to the command.

9. Feedback to MATLAB
• ESP32 sends status back to MATLAB (e.g., “Executing forward”).
• MATLAB displays the execution result in the Command Window.

10. Loop Until Exit
• System keeps listening for the next voice command.
• Exit when user presses Ctrl+C or gives a stop/quit command.
